❗️Army soldier Pavlo Petrychenko created a petition on the President's website to ban online casinos:

Dear Mr. President,
I, Pavlo Petrychenko, a soldier of the 59th brigade, want to draw your attention to the damage that the gambling business causes to the Ukrainian army and Ukrainian society.
Military personnel have been away from their families for the third year, in stressful conditions and without the possibility of full rest, so they are especially psychologically vulnerable. For many of them, gambling becomes the only way to cope with stress, and therefore quickly causes dopamine addiction and weakens their self-control. There are rare cases when game-addicted servicemen spend all their money on games and take microloans, thus putting themselves and their families in a "debt pit", or pawning drones and thermal imagers, thereby harming not only themselves, but also their fellow citizens .
Gambling businesses take advantage of this vulnerability by deliberately targeting military personnel, using symbols of the Armed Forces in their online casinos, and "whitewashing" their activities with small charitable donations to the Armed Forces.
In addition, many Russian online casinos target Ukrainian consumers in order to gain access to personal data of military personnel and other citizens, which poses a direct threat to the national security of our country. Huge debts of servicemen with gaming addiction can also become an element of pressure and manipulation by the special services of the aggressor country.
According to Article 93 of the Constitution of Ukraine, the President has the right of legislative initiative, and draft laws determined by the President of Ukraine as urgent are considered by the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine out of turn.
With this in mind, I ask you, Mr. President, to submit an urgent bill to the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine, which will provide for:

During martial law, the prohibition of gambling and access to online casinos for military personnel;

Prohibition of gambling advertising using the symbols of the Armed Forces, and any related symbols or items with war and the army, uniform, helmet, machine gun, etc.

Prohibition of charitable funds to cooperate with participants of the gambling market;

Prohibition of military units from accepting property in the form of charitable assistance from gambling market participants or related individuals or legal entities;

Prohibition of any advertising or public references to the fact that the participants of the gambling market provide charitable assistance to military personnel;

Prohibition of pawnshops from accepting drones, thermal imagers and other similar dual purpose goods;

Obligation of internet providers and mobile operators to block illegal casino websites.

